[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few ML libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 sagemaker pandas numpy scikit-learn xgboost
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `sagemaker:CreateTrainingJob`, `sagemaker:CreateModel`, `sagemaker:CreateEndpoint`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `sagemaker:CreateFeatureGroup`, `sagemaker:PutRecord`, `sagemaker:GetRecord`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject` (scoped to your training data bucket)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `iam:PassRole` (to pass the SageMaker execution role)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before we get to the steps, here's the configuration that drives the pipeline. These constants define feature schemas, model hyperparameters, and operational thresholds. They live at the top of your module so they're easy to find and tune.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import numpy as np
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import pandas as pd
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. In production, use JSON-formatted output for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # CloudWatch Logs Insights queries. Never log PHI (patient names,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # MRNs, diagnosis text).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Retry config for AWS API calls. Adaptive mode uses exponential backoff
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # with jitter, which handles burst throttling gracefully.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Feature Schema ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # These are the features the model expects, in order. The training pipeline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # and inference pipeline must produce features in this exact schema, or you
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # get training-serving skew (the #1 silent killer of ML model accuracy).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ADMISSION_FEATURES = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "age", "sex_encoded", "admission_source_encoded", "admission_type_encoded",
